    • Constructor Detail

      • ItDependsOn

        public ItDependsOn(Expression splitter,
                   ContextSplitting contextSplitting,
                   StepSolver<T> stepSolverIfSplitterIsTrue,
                   StepSolver<T> stepSolverIfSplitterIsFalse)
        Represents a solver step in which the final solution depends on the definition of a given expression by the context. Step solvers specialized for whether expression is true or false can be provided that already know about the definition of expression either way, for efficiency; however, if this step solver is provided instead, things still work because the step solver will end up determining anyway that expression is now defined and move on.
        Parameters:
        splitter -
        stepSolverIfSplitterIsTrue -
        stepSolverIfSplitterIsFalse -

        public StepSolver<T> getStepSolverForWhenSplitterIsTrue()
        Description copied from interface: StepSolver.Step
        Returns a StepSolver to be used for finding the final solution in case the splitter is defined as true by the context. This is merely an optimization, and using the original step solver should still work, but will perform wasted working re-discovering that expressions is already true.
